to open/to start/to initiate/to enlighten or awaken/to state/to inform

sentences.english: As he was getting the horse ready to set off, he found that the road was blocked.
sentences.chinese: 准备备马启程时，却发现路已经被堵死了。

sentences.english: He bade his wife farewell and set out on his journey.
sentences.chinese: 他辞别了妻子便启程了。

sentences.english: The lonely Ewok set out on a journey to find another village.
sentences.chinese: 这位孤独的伊渥克人启程去寻找另一个村落。

sentences.english: Please call again one week before your departure date for reconfirmation.
sentences.chinese: 请在您启程前一周再给我打一个电话落实一下。

sentences.english: I'm jumpin' in my ride, I'm heading out tonight.
sentences.chinese: 我在我的坐骑上雀跃，今夜我将启程。

sentences.english: Walk tired stop to have a rest, just remember the trip.
sentences.chinese: 走累了就停下来休息一会儿，只要还记得启程就好。

sentences.english: In July 1768 the Endeavour set out for the Pacific.
sentences.chinese: 1768年七月“奋力号”启程开赴太平洋。

sentences.english: Then finish the last song and let us leave.
sentences.chinese: 那末最后一曲终了就让我们启程吧。

sentences.english: Visa obtain departure scheduled saturday July1 st.
sentences.chinese: 已获签证，计划七月一日星期六启程。

sentences.english: Plum blossom spring, new year for quick action.
sentences.chinese: 寒梅绽放报春来，新年启程速行动。

sentences.english: He decided to leave at dawn , for he had a long way to go .
sentences.chinese: 他决定黎明启程，因为他还有很长的路要走。

sentences.english: The Black Hawks departed from Jalalabad thirty minutes later.
I hope we set our sails and venture out one day. That will be one glorious day… (8-22-2010)
sentences.chinese: 我希望有天我们能扬帆启程去冒险。

sentences.english: Probably was so masted when she set forth.
sentences.chinese: 在她启程时，大概桅杆直立，帆完全扯起。

sentences.english: After he had said goodbye to us all, Captain Alison started his journey.
sentences.chinese: 当艾利森船长和我们大家都道了别之后，他就启程了。

sentences.english: So together they drove througha pouring rain.
sentences.chinese: 于是他们一起冒雨开车启程。
